    • getResponseBody

      public io.netty.buffer.ByteBuf getResponseBody()
      N.B.: This function is backed by a Lazy property. The first time it is called, the response is recorded and will therefore not be regenerated even if the more records are added. To make this behavior unambiguous, it is no longer possible to add records after calling this function, as the records property then becomes an empty list.
